ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.
M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported
1 = In person; 2 = Phone; 3 = Mail; 4 = SIG-O only; 5 = Carp only

ElementDescription: In the PAST TWO WEEKS, have you seen a coach or a mentor?  This would be someone who is paid or volunteers to help you solve problems, or do fun things together.  This is not a therapist or counselor, case manager, social worker, or similar job to help you.
I saw the Coach twice each week.
My Coach teaches me skills that I need.
My Coach and I have fun together.
My Coach knows what my strengths are.
My Coach knows what interests me and what I like to do.
Overall, how satisfied were you with your Coach?
If you had the same need for help in the future, would you want to return to your Coach?
If you had a friend with the same need for help, would you recommend your Coach?
